The paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML). The proposed method involves learning a similarity function for classification, which is a technique commonly used in CV and ML. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves deep learning, which is a subfield of AI (Artificial Intelligence), making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper deals with classification, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing, which is a subfield of multimedia (MM), making cs.MM a possible sub-category.
